about: The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, commonly known as the United Kingdom (UK) or Britain, is a sovereign island country located off the north-western coast of Europe. It comprises four constituent countries: England, Scotland, Wales, and Northern Ireland. The UK is a parliamentary democracy and a constitutional monarchy, with Charles III as its current monarch. The country's capital city and largest metropolitan area is London. The UK is a maritime country, with a coastline extending over 11,000 miles. The island of Great Britain, which makes up most of the country's landmass, is divided into three countries: England, Scotland, and Wales. Northern Ireland occupies the northeastern part of the island of Ireland.
